<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">About this matrix</span><h2 class="h2">Methodology and citation</h2><p class="body"><strong>Purpose:</strong> A structured side-by-side comparison of the 12 AI vendors most often evaluated by B2B mid-market buyers in 2026. Designed for both buyers running real evaluations and analysts/journalists who need a citable comparison they can reference.</p><p class="body"><strong>Scope:</strong> General-purpose LLM platforms, IDE coding tools, and the major enterprise AI suite vendors. Excludes pure infrastructure (Bedrock, Vertex) and very vertical-specific tools.</p><div class="callout"><p><strong>Permission to cite:</strong> Yes. Attribution: "Treetop Growth Strategy, 2026 B2B AI Vendor Comparison Matrix, May 2026 — treetopgrowthstrategy.com/b2b-ai-vendor-comparison-matrix-2026". Stable URL; quarterly refresh.</p></div></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">General-purpose LLM platforms</span><h2 class="h2">Core comparison</h2><div class="table-wrap"><table class="t"><thead><tr><th>Feature</th><th>Claude (Anthropic)</th><th>ChatGPT (OpenAI)</th><th>Copilot (Microsoft)</th><th>Gemini (Google)</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Business tier</strong></td><td>Team \$30/u/mo</td><td>Team \$30/u/mo</td><td>M365 Copilot \$30/u/mo (req M365)</td><td>Business \$20/u/mo (req Workspace)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Enterprise tier</strong></td><td>Custom</td><td>Custom</td><td>Custom</td><td>Custom</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Default model class</strong></td><td>Sonnet 4.7</td><td>GPT-5</td><td>Mix (varies by surface)</td><td>Gemini Advanced</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Standard context window</strong></td><td>200K tokens</td><td>Variable, large</td><td>Variable</td><td>Large</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Max context window</strong></td><td>1M (some tiers)</td><td>Variable</td><td>Variable</td><td>Large</td></tr><tr><td><strong>SSO/SCIM</strong></td><td>Enterprise</td><td>Enterprise</td><td>Enterprise</td><td>Workspace tied</td></tr><tr><td><strong>BAA available</strong></td><td>Enterprise</td><td>Enterprise</td><td>Enterprise</td><td>Enterprise</td></tr><tr><td><strong>No training on inputs</strong></td><td>Team + Enterprise</td><td>Team + Enterprise</td><td>Business + Enterprise</td><td>Workspace tiers</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Custom Projects/GPTs</strong></td><td>Yes (Projects)</td><td>Yes (Custom GPTs)</td><td>Yes (Copilot Studio)</td><td>Yes (Gems)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Image generation</strong></td><td>Limited</td><td>Native</td><td>Limited</td><td>Native</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Web search</strong></td><td>Available</td><td>Native, polished</td><td>Native</td><td>Native</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Audio/voice</strong></td><td>Limited</td><td>Native</td><td>Limited</td><td>Native</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Strongest for</strong></td><td>Long-form writing, nuance, calibration</td><td>Breadth, ecosystem, multimodal</td><td>Microsoft-heavy stacks</td><td>Google Workspace customers</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Coding-focused tools</span><h2 class="h2">Engineering team comparison</h2><div class="table-wrap"><table class="t"><thead><tr><th>Feature</th><th>Claude Code</th><th>Cursor</th><th>GitHub Copilot</th><th>Windsurf</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Surface</strong></td><td>Terminal CLI</td><td>IDE (VS Code fork)</td><td>IDE inline + chat</td><td>IDE (VS Code fork)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Pricing (business)</strong></td><td>Claude Team/Ent + API</td><td>Pro \$20/u; Business \$40/u</td><td>Business \$19/u</td><td>Pro \$15/u</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Multi-file changes</strong></td><td>Strong (terminal-native)</td><td>Strong (Composer mode)</td><td>Limited</td><td>Moderate</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Large codebase reasoning</strong></td><td>Strong</td><td>Strong</td><td>Limited</td><td>Moderate</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Inline autocomplete</strong></td><td>N/A (terminal)</td><td>Strong</td><td>Strong</td><td>Strong</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Agentic workflows</strong></td><td>Strong</td><td>Strong</td><td>Limited</td><td>Moderate</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Best for</strong></td><td>Terminal-comfortable engineers, refactoring, large codebases</td><td>IDE workflows + agent</td><td>Microsoft/GitHub-heavy teams</td><td>IDE-based agent workflows</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Specialized AI vendor categories</span><h2 class="h2">What's commonly evaluated</h2><h3 class="h3">Conversation intelligence + sales recording</h3><ul class="ul"><li><strong>Gong</strong> — market leader; recording + transcription + insights. Insights features mixed quality; recording + search still highest value.</li><li><strong>Chorus</strong> — Zoominfo-owned; similar capability set to Gong; tighter Zoominfo integration.</li><li><strong>Fathom</strong> — lighter-weight; growing among smaller teams.</li><li><strong>Granola</strong> — newer; AI-native note-taking layered on recording; popular with execs.</li></ul><h3 class="h3">Customer service AI</h3><ul class="ul"><li><strong>Gorgias</strong> — DTC/ecommerce focus; AI draft + agent assist features.</li><li><strong>Intercom (Fin)</strong> — AI agent product; strong adoption; quality varies by use case.</li><li><strong>Zendesk AI</strong> — built into the existing platform; reasonable but rarely lead reason to choose Zendesk.</li><li><strong>Front (with AI features)</strong> — shared inbox with AI draft.</li></ul><h3 class="h3">AI for marketing operations</h3><ul class="ul"><li><strong>HubSpot (with AI features)</strong> — native AI across the platform; usually best to use what's already in the stack.</li><li><strong>Salesforce Einstein</strong> — improving; pricing premium often substantial.</li><li><strong>Various 'AI marketing platforms'</strong> — most are thin wrappers on Claude/GPT; usually replaceable by Claude/ChatGPT Project work.</li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Decision guidance by buyer profile</span><h2 class="h2">Which combo fits which company</h2><div class="table-wrap"><table class="t"><thead><tr><th>Buyer profile</th><th>Recommended primary platform</th><th>Recommended add-ons</th><th>Skip</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>B2B SaaS \$5M-\$20M, technical team</td><td>Claude Team</td><td>Claude Code or Cursor for engineering; Gong for sales recording</td><td>Multi-vendor AI stacks; specialized AI suites</td></tr><tr><td>Professional services firm, mixed tech</td><td>Claude Team</td><td>Standard transcription (Fathom/Otter)</td><td>Vertical-specific AI for verticals you do not serve</td></tr><tr><td>Microsoft-heavy enterprise (50+)</td><td>Microsoft Copilot</td><td>GitHub Copilot for engineering</td><td>Adding Claude unless specific gap</td></tr><tr><td>Google Workspace-heavy team</td><td>Gemini Business</td><td>Add Claude for writing-heavy workflows</td><td>Microsoft Copilot</td></tr><tr><td>DTC e-commerce</td><td>Claude Team</td><td>Gorgias AI for CS; Klaviyo for lifecycle</td><td>Specialized "AI for DTC" platforms</td></tr><tr><td>Regulated industry (healthcare, finserv)</td><td>Claude Enterprise (BAA) or ChatGPT Enterprise</td><td>Industry-specific tooling vetted for compliance</td><td>Free or consumer tiers, ever</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Pricing pitfalls</span><h2 class="h2">Common buyer mistakes</h2><ul class="ul"><li><strong>Buying multiple horizontal LLM platforms.</strong> One platform deeply adopted beats two platforms shallowly adopted, every time.</li><li><strong>Paying for AI features in existing tools you do not use.</strong> Audit what's in your stack before adding.</li><li><strong>Enterprise tier when Team would suffice.</strong> If you don't specifically need SSO, SCIM, or BAA, Team tier saves 40-60%.</li><li><strong>API + UI double-pay.</strong> Building custom AI features on the API while also paying for UI seats — only do this if both surfaces are genuinely used.</li><li><strong>Bundled pricing surprises.</strong> Microsoft Copilot requires M365; Gemini Business requires Workspace. Factor in the base license.</li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">What's likely to change in the next 12 months</span><h2 class="h2">Vendor trajectory predictions</h2><ul class="ul"><li><strong>Capability convergence continues.</strong> Frontier model gap between Claude, GPT, Gemini narrows further. Differentiation moves to integration, workflow, and price.</li><li><strong>Specialized 'AI feature' SaaS gets squeezed.</strong> Thin-wrapper vendors lose ground as horizontal LLM platforms absorb their capabilities.</li><li><strong>Coding tool category consolidates.</strong> 2-3 winners emerge from the current 6-8 contenders. Cursor and Claude Code currently leading among engineers we observe.</li><li><strong>Enterprise tier becomes more flexible.</strong> SSO, audit, BAA features expand to lower tiers; the rationale to upgrade narrows.</li><li><strong>'AI in your existing CRM/helpdesk/marketing tool' improves substantially.</strong> Re-evaluate dismissed AI features in tools you already pay for, in 6-12 months.</li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Methodology</span><h2 class="h2">How this matrix is maintained</h2><ul class="ul"><li>Vendor pricing and feature data reviewed May 12-18, 2026.</li><li>Buyer evaluation feedback aggregated across ~60 mid-market engagements.</li><li>Capability assessments based on direct usage and structured comparison tests.</li><li>Subjective ratings ("strong," "moderate," "limited") reflect Treetop's evaluation; reasonable people may disagree.</li><li>Refresh cadence: quarterly. Next refresh: August 2026.</li></ul></div></section>

